  "prompt": "Will Batman v Superman: Dawn of Justice flop?",
  "response": "\"Batman v Superman: Dawn of Justice\" was released in 2016, so we can look at its performance after release to determine whether it flopped. The film had a mixed reception: it was a box office success but received generally negative reviews from critics.\n\nFinancially, \"Batman v Superman\" grossed over $870 million worldwide against a production budget of around $250 million. This makes it a commercial success, as it earned back significantly more than its production costs. However, it did not meet some industry expectations of crossing the $1 billion mark.\n\nCritically, the movie received mixed to negative reviews. It holds a relatively low score on Rotten Tomatoes and Metacritic, with critics often citing issues with the film's pacing, tone, and script. Despite this, it has a considerably more positive reception among certain segments of the audience.\n\nIn summary, while it did not flop financially, it faced criticism that affected its reputation in some quarters.",
